attributes.logicalName: Account Affiliated With Prime Broker Flag
attributes.gcd: Flag indicates whether or not this account is affiliated with a prime broker. List of values are Y, N.

Refers to the date on which the account is closed. Account can be an active or closed, this column will remain blank till account is active. Accounts can be closed upon maturity, transfer or death of a customer.
Refers to account name which should be displayed in the account. This is often the name of the primary customer on the account.
Refers to the total gross value of all assets associated with this account expressed in account currency. This is the aggregate value of all holdings in this account, cash plus securities.

Refers to the unique identifier of the account group to which this account is assigned. Account group is a grouping of accounts based on certain criteria. Examples of account group types include household, statement bundling etc.

Refers to the account manager is an employee who is responsible for the day to day management of accounts of a particular customer. The account manager is a point of contact, and provides customer support, up selling, technical assistance and general relationship management. An account manager may be in charge of a number of smaller accounts, or may focus on a few larger accounts. This column Refers to the account manager code or the unique employee identifier of the manager assigned by the financial institution. Management Dimension is the equivalent dimension table for this column.

Refers to the total net value of all assets associated with this account expressed in the account currency. This is the aggregate value of all holdings in this account, with a reduction for any margin loans or other debts owed to the financial institution.

Refers to the date on which the account was opened in the financial institution. This is the system date on which the financial institution opens the account. It may or may not be equal to effective date.
Flag to indicate if the account is closed. Account can be closed upon maturity of the account, transfer of the account, death of the account holder or write off.

Refers to the unique identifier of the account or contract held by the customer. Account number is defined as numbers, letters or alphanumeric code assigned to every significant customer, supplier and lender for ease of reference in accounting records of the financial institution.
Refers to the amount outstanding priced at cash advance APR at the end of the cycle. At the end refers to the balance as of statement date.
Refers to the purpose for which account has originated, purpose or special use of this account. Account purpose dimension is the equivalent dimension table for this column.

Refers to the unique code of the status of the account. List of values can be Active, Inactive, in foreclosure, Re negotiated, Dispute, Frozen, Past Due, Closed etc. Account Status Dimension is the equivalent dimension table for this column.
Refers to the date on which the current account status became effective.
Refers to the Account Sub Type Code that is sub classified as per the banking source system for their internal operational purpose.

Refers to the actual title of the account. This attribute is needed to identify whether the title of the account contains the name of an unincorporated association. For example in FDIC depending on whether the account title contains the name of the unincorporated association, the classification for deposit insurance as per FDIC differs. In case for Insurance companies, Refers to Name of the security, address for property.

Refers to the Account Type Code that is classified as per the banking source system for their internal operational purpose. 
In case of ALM FTP applications, Account type are fixed set of values.
Refers to the date on which the account verification profile letter was sent for a profile.

Refers to the unique code of the accounting standard or the rules to which accountants adhere when preparing financial statements to ensure minimum level of consistency. E.g. GAAP, IFRS etc. Generally Accepted Accounting Principles, GAAP. GAAP are the rules to which accountants adhere when preparing financial statements to ensure minimum level of consistency. The Generally Accepted Accounting Principles exist to ensure that accountants are using the same or almost the same standards so that comparison of financial statements between or within a company is easy and accurate. They also promote transparency in accounting. However, GAAP provides broad guidelines, there is room for companies to follow an approach within a guideline.
Refers to the channel through which customer was acquired.
Refers to the unique identifier for adjustment type dimension at an account. Examples can be CONTRA,NEW etc.

attributes.logicalName: Amount Due In Next Twelve Months
attributes.gcd: Refers to the Amount Due In Next 12 Months.
Refers to the date as on which the snapshot of source data extracted for processing.

Refers to the monthly Average balance. There are different ways to compute monthly average balance. A simple method would be, Opening balance Plus Closing Balance, divided by 2. A complex method would be find out for how many days the balance was with the Financial Institution and then compute the average balance.
Refers to the Booking Center associated with this account and is applicable in Private Banking.

Refers to the branch code. A branch, banking center or financial center is a retail location where a financial institution offers a wide array of face to face and automated services to its customers. This column Refers to the unique branch code assigned by the financial institution. A branch may specialize to offer certain type of products to customers. Branch needs approval from the regulators.
Refers to the brokerage plan code associated with this trading account.
Refers to the total base currency market value of securities held with broker.
Refers to the unique identifier of the business domain., such as Institutional or Retail Brokerage. This is used to control access to data across distinct business operations.
Refers to the level of risk associated with this account with respect to business characteristics. List of values are in the range of 0 10 with increasing values denoting increasing risk levels.

Refers to the business unit code as defined by the organization. A business unit is generally a broader definition and represents all the units in an organization. Business Unit dimension is the equivalent dimension table for this column.

Refers to the unique identifier of the campaign under which the account was acquired. Campaign is defined as Specific activities designed to promote a product, service or business. A marketing campaign is a coordinated series of steps that can include promotion of a product through different mediums like television, radio, print, online using a variety of different types of advertisements. The campaign doesn't have to rely solely on advertising, and can also include demonstrations, word of mouth and other interactive techniques. Campaigns are created or started by financial institutions to promote sales, improve visibility of the brand or product and create opportunities for addon sales and cross selling.
Refers to the amount of collateral expressed in account currency that this account is obliged to provide based on the activities it is performing.
This is the degree of risk, the customer is willing to take on investments in this account.
Refers to the number of distinct customers to whom statements are mailed for this account. These are the customers which are associated with the account.

Refers to the mantas classification associated with this record. This can be a jurisdiction which represents geographical or legal entity monitoring on data restrictions. Values can be AMEA, INDV, CORP etc.

Refers to the source system from where data is extracted. Data can be sourced from multiple sources, this column will Refers to the source code from where the data is extracted for this extraction date.

Flag indicates if it is a DvP, Delivery Versus Payment, or RvP, Receive Versus Payment, trade or not. Delivery versus payment, DVP, is a settlement system that stipulates that cash payment must be made prior to or simultaneously with the delivery of the security. Delivery versus payment is from the perspective of buyer and from the perspective of seller, this system is called receive versus payment, RVP. For DvP transactions, if the payments have not yet taken place five business days after the settlement date, firms must calculate a capital charge by multiplying the positive current exposure of the transaction by the appropriate factor, according to a Table given by Basel. List of values are Y, N. Y indicates it is a DVP.
Refers to the digital wallet address.

Refers to the aggregate gross amount of dividends paid or credited with respect to an account being reported for the calendar year except certain gross proceeds from the sale or redemption of property.
Refers to the effective date of the account or contract or interest rate or exchange rate from which it is effective.
Flag indicates whether an employee of the financial institution has a personal association on this account, either through a direct customer role or a family member relationship.
Refers to the total market value of all long equity positions in this account expressed in account currency.
Refers to the total market value of all short equity positions in this account expressed in account currency.

Refers to the account`s margin equity value as a percentage of its total marginable holdings. This figure is used to trigger margin maintenance calls. For instance a value of 89 Percent will be stored as 89 and a value of 89.45 will be rounded to nearest integer.
Refers to the excess margin amount for the reporting entity’s customer to generate funding for additional purchases or short sales of securities or others.

Refers to the FATCA Pool Report Code. List of values are FATCA201  Recalcitrant account holders with US Indicia, FATCA202  Recalcitrant account holders without US Indicia, FATCA203  Dormant Accounts, FATCA204  Non participating foreign financial institutions, FATCA205  Recalcitrant account holders that are US persons and FATCA206  Recalcitrant account holders that are passive Non Financial Foreign Entities.

Refers to the FATCA reporting period end date. This date is the date on which the net worth is reported at the account level for FATCA purpose. This is used in conjunction with the column FATCA Reporting Period Net Worth Amount.

attributes.logicalName: Fatca Reporting Period Net Worth Amount
attributes.gcd: Refers to the FATCA Reporting Period Net worth amount. This is the total net value of all assets associated with this account expressed in base currency as of the end of the last reporting period. This is the aggregate value of all holdings in this account, with a reduction for any margin loans or other debts owed.

Refers to the FATCA Status Code. List of values are INDETER  Indeterminate, RECALC  Recalcitrant, USP  US Person, NPFFI  Non Participating Foreign Financial Institution, PAS NFFE  Passive Non Financial Foreign Entity, ACT NFFE  Active Non Financial Foreign Entity, PFFI  Participating Foreign Financial Institution, EXC NFFE  Excepted Non Financial Foreign Entity, OWNER.

Flag indicates if the account is held with the bank under a fiduciary capacity. Fiduciary capacity means trustee, executor, administrator, registrar of stocks and bonds, transfer agent, guardian, assignee, receiver, or custodian under a uniform gifts to minors act investment adviser, if the bank receives a fee for its investment advice any capacity in which the bank possesses investment discretion on behalf of another or any other similar capacity that the regulator authorizes. For example deposits that are placed with a bank by a national bank for which the bank is a fiduciary.

Refers to the liabilities of a broker or dealer to customers which are subject to immediate cash resulting from sales of securities, dividends, interest, deposits, or otherwise. payment whether resulting from sales of securities, dividends, interest, deposits, or otherwise. These balances should be net of any debit balances, customer receivables, in related accounts.
Refers to the free credit amount. Free credit balances are the cash that a client has a right to demand on short notice. This is required for prime brokers in US to collect their clients free credit balances “in safe areas of the broker dealers business related to servicing its customers” or to otherwise deposit the funds in a reserve bank account to prevent commingling of customer and firm funds.
Refers to the unique general ledger account code.
Refers to the level of geographical risk associated with this account. List of values are in the range of 0 10 with increasing values denoting increasing risk levels.
Flag indicates if this account is a part of a global or major corporate relationship, that is, one of several accounts held with a large, trusted customer, List of Values are Y = Yes, N= No.
Refers to the aggregate gross proceeds from the sale or redemption of property paid or credited to the account being reported for the calendar year.
Flag indicates if this account has a high activity level in terms of trades or other transactions.
Flag indicates whether this account is a high profile or preferred account that prove to be a conflict of interest while managing the assets of portfolio of accounts. List of values are Y, N.
Flag indicates whether the hold all mail flag applicable to this account.
Refers to the household identifier of which this account is a member. Households are groups of related accounts, which may or may not have the same mailing address.

Refers to the country code associated with the business. There are several popular country codes as part of ISO 3166 standard published by the International Organization for Standardization. ISO 3166 defines codes for the names of countries, dependent territories, special areas of geographical interest and their principal subdivisions. In case of party, it Refers to the country of birth of the party.

ISO currency codes is a standard published by the International Organization for Standardization 4217, which delineates currency designators and country codes, alpha and numeric. This column will capture the standardized currency code. Currency dimension is the equivalent dimension table for this column.
Refers to the ISO State code of the Address. International Organization for Standardization, ISO, and defines codes for each state.
Refers to the aggregate gross amount of interest paid or credited to the account being reported for the calendar year except certain gross proceeds from the sale or redemption of property.
Flag indicates if the account or transaction is belongs to an international banking facility. List of Values are Y and N.
Refers to the date on which this account requested approval for intra-day trading.
Refers to the account's approval status for intra-day trading.

attributes.logicalName: Intra-Day Trading Approval Status Last Update Date
attributes.gcd: Refers to the date on which this account's intra-day trading approval status was last updated.
Refers to the identifier of the user who performed the last update to this account's intra-day trading approval status.
Refers to the identifier of the investment advisor, an individual, or firm that manages this account.
Refers to the name of the investment advisor that manages this account.
Flag indicates whether if this customer account is referred to an investment advisor by the financial institution.
Refers to the investment officer code associated with this account. Investment officer is defined as the executive position responsible for a company's investment portfolios.
Refers to the investment style (if specified) at the trading account level. List of indicative values can be Active, Passive etc.

Refers to the date on which the last activity happens on an account. Activity on an account can be referred to anything like withdrawal from an account, deposit in account etc. The Activity date is generally for customer initiated transaction and not for system initiated transaction like interest liquidation, debiting charges etc.
Refers to the immediate past date on which the last account statement was generated on this account.
Refers to the entity code of the legal entity to which the account will be attributed in the general ledger.

Refers to line of business, LOB, is a functional unit that offers the products to the customer by the financial entity. Example: Corporate Finance, Trade Services, Private Wealth Management, Treasury Services, Retail Banking, Cards services etc. Refers to the unique code of the line of business applicable to the respective product.

Refers to the load run identifier. Load run identifier enables user to load multiple versions intraday or post back dated adjustment entries to the table. Refers to the Load run identifier of the equivalent record in product processor that needs to be adjusted. Default value of  1 indicates that the latest load run is being adjusted.
Refers to the unique location code. Location code is defined as the code which will represent the address of the property from zip code onwards like which city, country etc.

Refers to the amount required under applicable legal requirements for the protection of customer assets with respect to each broker-dealer segregated account, in accordance with the reporting entity’s normal frequency of recalculating such requirements.

Refers to the frequency of fee payment for fee based accounts. List of valid values: D-Daily, W-Weekly, B- Bi-Weekly, T-Fortnightly, M-Monthly, Q-Quarterly, A-Annually, S-Semi-Annually and N- Bi-Monthly (every 2 months).

Refers to the equity maintenance requirement for this account. The account receives a margin call if its equity percentage drops below this level. For instance a value of 89 Percent will be stored as 89 and a value of 89.45 will be rounded to nearest integer.

Flag indicates if particular account is managed or not. Here “managed” refers to loans originated by the Bank Holding Company, including securitized loans put back on the books due to ASC Topics 860 which deals with transfers and servicing arrangements and 810 which deal with consolidation of entity. However it does not include loans that were originated by a third party and only serviced by the BHC. List of values are Y,N.

Total net value of all assets associated with this account. This is the aggregate value of all holdings in this account, with a reduction for any margin loans or other debts owed to the financial institution. Expressed in base currency.

Refers to the Mantas defined internal or external customer type that uses this account. This will be used for identifying Mantas defined customer types relevant to financial crime compliance based on set of rules. Expected values are  CR - Retail Customer CI - Institutional Customer IA - Investment Advisor CO - Correspondent Financial Institution EE - Employee or Family Member FP - Firm Trading FO - Firm Owned, Non-Trading FA - Firm Administrative FE - Firm Error or Suspense DC - Clearing Organization IS - Issuer or Writer.
Refers to the functional area in which this account is used. List of valid values are: RBR- Retail Brokerage/Private Client, IBR- Institutional Brokerage and PRP- Proprietary.
This is the control group code used to identify a control group with which this account is associated.
Refers to the margin utilised for an outstanding position with the broker.
Refers to the net value of this account’s holdings in marginable assets (that is, its total margin holdings less any margin debt owed to the financial institution). Expressed in account currency.
Refers to the value of the long positions that are held on margin in this account, expressed in account currency.
Refers to the value of the short positions that are held on margin in this account, expressed in account currency.
Indicator of whether this account has been approved for margin trading.
Identifier of the master account that the investment advisor uses to manage this customer account.
Refers to the name of the master account that the investment advisor uses to manage this customer account.
Refers to the total market value of all money market fund security positions in this account, expressed in account currency.

Refers to the value of the assets expressed in account currency that have been provided as collateral in this account. This amount represents the net value that can be counted toward collateral obligations, after applying any reductions based on the volatility or liquidity of the assets involved.
Refers to the next calculation Date.
Refers to next margin calculation Date.

Flag to indicate whether the account information change letter has been suppressed for this account means the customer does not want to receive notification for the changes done on the account. If the Y, then the customer should not be notified of changes to account information such as address or phone number and if the value is N means the customer should be notified of any changes on the account.

Refers to the unique identifier of the offer. An offer is defined as an abstract, physical and or monetary benefit attached to a product for a predetermined period of time with a view to increase the sales of a product. Offer dimension is the equivalent dimension table for this column.

attributes.logicalName: Office Of Foreign Asset Control Reason Indicator
attributes.gcd: Indicates the OFAC reason indicator for this account. List of valid values are: O OFAC Freeze, P  Patriot Act Freeze, V  Patriot Verification, F  Systematic CIP Freeze, D  Compliance CIP Override and N  Registered Principle. Office Of Foreign Asset Control, OFAC, is defined by the department of the U.S. Treasury that enforces economic and trade sanctions against countries and groups of individuals involved in terrorism, narcotics and other disreputable activities.

Refers to the option approval code for this account. List of values are: A- Short Covered, Buy Put and Call Options and Spreads; B- Equity Short Covered Call (Cash & Margin); C- Short Covered Calls; D- Short Covered and Uncovered options, Buy Put and Call Options and Spreads, E- Equity All Strategies; F- Option Approval Rejected: Awaiting Documents; G- Option Approval Rejected; H- Short Covered, Buy Put and Call options; I- Incomplete, Option Form not received; J- Short Covered, Buy Put and Call Options; K- Option Approval: Branch Restricted; L- No Option Trading; M- Short Covered, Uncovered Put, Buy Call and Put Options and Spreads; N- Short Covered, Buy Put, Long Options Spreads and Debt Underlying; O- Missing; P- Short Covered Calls including debt options; Q- Equity and Debt Buy or Sell Covered Calls only; R- Short Covered and Uncovered, Buy Options and Spreads including debt options; T- Short Covered, Buy Put and Call Options and Spreads including debt options; U- Option Approval Unknown; V- Equity and Debt- All Strategies; W- Option Approval Trading Restriction due to insufficient Documents; X- Option Approval Trading Restriction due to additional violations; Y- Restriction on Options due to Surveillance; Z- No Option Trading Allowed.
Refers to the date on which this account was approved for its current level of options trading.
Refers to the options trading approval type for this account (for example, approval to trade uncovered options).
Refers to the amount of cash collateral this account is obliged to provide in order to cover potential exposure from uncovered options or credit spread option positions expressed in account currency.
Refers to the total market value of all long option positions in this account, expressed in account currency.
Refers to the total market value of all short option positions in this account, expressed in account currency.
Refers to the cost center to which the account belongs to. Organization Unit dimension is the equivalent dimension table for this column.

Refers to the original account number held by the source system. If there are multiple source systems without unique account numbers, we expect the account number and source system to be concatenated as part of the primary key, while this column will store the original account number as generated by the source system.
The aggregate gross amount of all income paid or credited to an account for the calendar year, reduced by interest, dividends, and gross proceeds.

Refers to the organization defined code for the ownership type of the account. Expected values are IND  Individual, JOINT  Joint Tenant or Community Property, TRUST  Trust, CUST  Custodian, CORP  Corporate, FIRM  Firm Owned and OTHER  Other.
Refers to the unique identifier for the party. Party is defined as an entity or a person who takes part or is involved in an agreement, lawsuit, or transaction.
Flag indicates whether a trader shows a pattern of day trading in this account.
Indicator of how the customer compensates the financial institution. E.g., F-Fee, C-Commission or B-both.
Refers to the date on which the payment basis begins.
Refers to the identifier for a specific account that is unique across the enterprise for the lifetime of the account. This identifier is not subject to tricking.
Refers to the identifier of the Portfolio Manager who is responsible for managing the assets in this account.

attributes.logicalName: Power Of Attorney Or Signatory Flag
attributes.gcd: Flag to indicate whether this account has power of attorney or signatory authority granted to a person with a US address. . This is required for FATCA purpose. List of values are Y, N. If the value is updated as Y means this account has power of attorney granted to a person with a US address and if the value is updated as N means the power of attorney is not granted to a person with US address or this account does not have any power of attorney.
Refers to the primary product traded in this account (for example UIS Treasuries, Futures, Options). List of values can be : Equities, Corporate Debt, Sovereign Debt, Futures, Options etc.

Flag indicates if the account is associated with prime brokerage services. Prime brokerage is the generic name for a bundled package of services offered by investment banks and securities firms to hedge funds and other professional investors. List of values are Y, N.
Refers to the unique code assigned to each of the Products offered by the Bank.

Flag indicates whether this account is considered to be a recalcitrant account. A Recalcitrant account is defined as an account that, 1, fails to comply with reasonable requests for information pursuant to IRS mandated verification and due diligence procedures to identify US Accounts,, 2, fails to provide a name, address and taxpayer identification number or, 3, fails to provide a bank secrecy waiver upon request. List of values are Y, N.
Refers to the record creation date. It has been added to all catalog entities to enable partitioning and archival.

Refers to the geographical grouping of the market based on certain common characteristics like language, ethnicity, country, continent, city and state. The region can vary based on the definition of market. Global market vs local market can have different definition of region.
Refers to the client relationship to which this account belongs.
Refers to the reporting currency code. Usually, it is the currency code of the country in which the financial institution that owns the account operates.
Flag indicates whether this customer account was originally a retail account that was later referred to this investment advisor.
Refers to the Segment Identifier value.

Refers to the service level code applicable to this account. Banks generally have levels of services, some of which are available for a fee. The levels may be structured in a cumulative fashion where the next level consists of the prior level services plus services for the level itself.
Identifier of the service team that is responsible for servicing this account.
Refers to the source from where the initial funds will come as stated by the customer for the account, e.g. salary, lottery, etc..
Flag indicates whether the account holder for this account is a speculative investor.
Refers to the speculation level indicator of the account holder. List of values may be in the range of 0-4 with 0 indicating no speculation and 4 indicating highest speculation level.

attributes.logicalName: Standing Instructions To Us Account Flag
attributes.gcd: Flag to indicate whether there are standing instructions to transfer funds from this account to an account maintained in the United States. This is required for FATCA purpose. If the value is updated as Y means there are standing instructions to transfer funds to US account and if the value is updated as N means there are no instructions to transfer funds from the account to US account.

Flag to indicate whether the distribution of statements is suppressed for this account. Normally it is done to switch to paperless where customer will always have access to his records online. If the value is updated as Y means the distribution of statement is suppressed and if the value is updated as N means the distribution of statement is not suppressed for the account.
Refers to the stock option plan indicator applicable to this trading account. List of Values Y = Yes, N= No.

Refers to the indicator of how closely this account is monitored for risk and suitability issues. The value of this field could be based on the programs/offerings in which the account participates, the features/characteristics of the account, and/or the account's prior activity.
For fee-based accounts, the amount of commissions that would have been charged if this were a commission-based account.
Refers to the unique code of the customer who is responsible for paying taxes on this account. Customer Dimension is the equivalent dimension table for this column.
Refers to the aggregate value of all holdings in this account, expressed in account currency. This is equal to this account’s net worth plus its outstanding debts.

Refers to the net unsecured debt for this account expressed in account currency. This is the amount by which the debt owed to the financial institution exceeds the aggregate value of the holdings in this account.
Refers to all the fee collected from the customer for the period expressed in account currency.
Refers to the total liquid assets in this account that are available for payment or withdrawal expressed in the account currency.
Indicator of whether the investment advisor associated with this account has discretion to execute trades on behalf of its account owner.
Refers to the pledge indicator for this trading account. If any pledge agreements are set for this trading account, the value will be 'Y', else the value will be 'N'.

Refers to the unique identifier of the trading desk that has entered into a trade. Banks has various trading desks specializing for specific products, like Interest Rate Products, Equity, Commodities, etc.

Refers to the unique identification code for a treatment. Treatment is defined which is channel specific instance of an offer. Treatment Refers to the message associated with the offer. Treatment dimension is the equivalent dimension table for this column.
Refers to the undrawn portion of the margin amount i.e. the unfunded contractual commitment to lend to a brokerage customer on margin for a specified duration.

attributes.logicalName: Unrealized Profit Or Loss - Inception Till Date
attributes.gcd: Refers to the Monetary value of the profit or loss unrealized in this account from inception to date expressed in base currency. This value is the difference in aggregate market value from the time the product was purchased to submission date for all securities held through that period.

attributes.logicalName: Unrealized Profit Or Loss - Year Till Date
attributes.gcd: Refers to the Monetary value of the profit or loss unrealized in this account from the beginning of the year to date expressed in base currency.

Flag indicates if the account has US Indicia. US Indicia indicates presence of any of the following: US Citizenship or lawful or permanent resident, US birth place, US address, Instructions to transfer funds to US Accounts or directions regularly received from a US address etc. List of values are Y, N.
